
---
import workshopImage from "../assets/team/workshop.webp";
---
<section id="about" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">

      <!-- Title -->
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 leading-tight mb-6 animate-on-scroll">
      Secure and Private System Design for Generative & Agentic AI
      </h2>

      <!-- Time & Location -->
      <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-1 animate-on-scroll">
        <span class="font-bold">Time:</span> 9:00 - 17:00 (PDT), July 26, 2026
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-8 animate-on-scroll">
        <span class="font-bold">Location:</span> 	Mtg Room 101A, Long Beach (Co-located with DAC 2026)
      </p>

      <!-- Image -->
      <div class="mb-10 animate-on-scroll">
        <img
          src={workshopImage.src}
          alt="Workshop Venue"
         class="w-1/2 max-w-sm mx-auto rounded-lg shadow-md object-cover"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Description -->
      <div class="text-left animate-on-scroll">
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-justify">
         The SPGAI workshop at DAC 2026 will focus on how to ensure the security, privacy, and verifiability of generative and agentic AI systems used in EDA automation, chip design, and semiconductor development. It is the first cross-layer forum at DAC dedicated to this topic, aiming to address emerging challenges as AI systems generate RTL, verify designs, interact with sensitive intellectual property, and operate autonomously across complex toolchains. The workshop will bring together leading researchers and industry practitioners to integrate advances in cryptography, hardware architecture, verifiable computing, AI security, and design automation. It will feature keynotes, technical presentations, and interactive discussions, and will provide new methods, system frameworks, and evaluation approaches for building trustworthy AI systems in hardware and EDA workflows.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
